<subSubSection id="5033E67092744CD1FFD8FB9DEB10032A" pageId="0" pageNumber="131" type="phenology">
<paragraph id="AE2169F6297F341264D501EB8E10A300" pageId="0" pageNumber="131">Phenology.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D6FB99D30E6455832CF1687C320A2D93" pageId="0" pageNumber="131">Flowering from October to December, fruiting from November to January next year.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="A2DFE40EB94ED50FEE725631770DEB51" pageId="0" pageNumber="131" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="17A67A313790BDDCD4917B1FB891BDE7" pageId="0" pageNumber="131">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="99A7F2F3C3A9DC014372FE99FB3109CC" pageId="0" pageNumber="131">The epithet of the new species refers to its suffrutescent habit, which is distinct in the genus.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
