<subSubSection id="1B7A42A0497D897A653D8156AB64F97B" pageId="0" pageNumber="131" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="4A283B2043EB9A2E5F64A3FE821E5110" pageId="0" pageNumber="131">Distribution and habitat.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="63DD7623A5EC58180B1DAB9CED00293B" pageId="0" pageNumber="131">
<taxonomicName id="21F078C11842E17CA9F41540C30B737E" authorityName="Y. P. Chen, A. J. Paton &amp; C. L. Xiang" authorityYear="2020" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lamiaceae" genus="Hanceola" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Hanceola suffruticosa" order="Lamiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="131" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="suffruticosa">
<emphasis id="8080449ECB4A25C49C87DEA909E019AD" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="131">Hanceola suffruticosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is now only known at the Sino-Vietnamese border of Malipo County in Yunnan Province, China and Quan Ba District of Ha Giang Province, Vietnam (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="29E809146525C66A756A083BF15A1DE4" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. Distribution of Hanceola suffruticosa (stars)." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.145.49995.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/399202" pageId="0" pageNumber="131">3</figureCitation>
). It grows in the evergreen mixed forests at an elevation of 1100-1150 m.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
